superMiscConds.notes:
Defendant shall pay supervisory fees to the Department of Corrections;
Defendant shall complete any/all counseling, evaluations, assessments, and follow-up as deemed appropriate, to include Sex Offender Counseling and psychological evaluation;
Defendant shall not possess/consume any alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
Defendant shall not enter any establishment in which their primary purpose is the sale of alcohol;
Defendant shall not have contact with or employment with anyone under 18 years of age unless supervised;
Defendant shall not possess any electronic device that access the internet.  If becomes employed and use of computer is necessary, Defendant must inform employer of this case;
Lifetime Sex Offender Registration;
Defendant shall submit a DNA sample if not previously submitted and pay costs.

